 {
  "text": "Hi, my name is Mariana. Let me tell you about my morning at the store. I want to buy a new dress for a party. I see a beautiful red dress, but the price is very high. It is expensive: two hundred reais. So I ask the assistant: How much is the blue dress? The blue dress is cheap, only sixty reais. I am very happy. I pay with my card, and I buy the blue dress. Now I have a new dress for the party.",
  "voice": "ellen",
  "file": "a10_listening1.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "Hello, I am Gustavo. On Saturday I go to the market near my house. I like the market because the food is cheap. I buy bread, fruit and water for my family. I always ask the price first: How much is the bread? How many apples do you want? The man says four reais for the bread. I have a little money, so I buy only the things I need. The market is cheap, and I do not pay a lot. I am a smart shopper.",
  "voice": "arthur",
  "file": "a10_listening2.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "First, I go into the store. Second, I look at the shirts. Third, I ask how much the shirt is. Fourth, I pay with my card. Fifth, I take my new shirt home.",
  "voice": "ellen",
  "file": "pc10_order_l10.mp3"
 },
